  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason: The proposed extension of the  front steps and the installation of balustrades on either side, by reason of its inappropriate design, scale, massing and excessive depth and height, would form a discordant feature when viewed from the street and would have a detrimental effect on the architectural significance and appearance of the host locally listed building and the wider surrounding conservation area. The development is therefore considered to be contrary to policy 9 of Islington’s Core Strategy 2011, policies D4 (Designing in context), D8 (Boundary walls, paving and street furniture) D11 (Alterations and extensions), of Islington’s Unitary Development Plan 2002, Islington’s Urban Design Guidance 2006,  St Mary Magdelene Conservation Guidance Note   and PPS 5"
